In this way, feelings are closely linked to the regions of the Cortex, which distinguish primates and, in particular, people.
Related to the linguistic nature, fine classifications of feeling arise because with the help of the words and grammar we can differentiate and categorize states in order to attribute them to others besides ourselves.
