Dark matter influenced flight by space probes
For years, a mysterious phenomenon in researchers has created an intrusion: Dark matter influences the speed of space probes during so-called swing-by maneuvers.
Experts fear that the general relativity theory of Albert Einstein could not be quite right.
Almost 18 years the space probe "Ulysses" flew through space.
